{"name":"Turn Undead","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>All clerics can exert control over the undead and some d&aelig;monic beings, causing them to flee and/or cower. Evil clerics can opt instead to compel the submission and service of these foul creatures. In either case, the cleric must do the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Stand before the undead (within 30 feet)</li>\n<li>Speak boldly a commandment whilst displaying a holy symbol</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The referee must cross-reference the cleric&rsquo;s <em>turning ability</em> (TA) with the <em>Undead Type</em> to determine the cleric&rsquo;s chance of success. The referee may ask the player to roll a d12 to determine the outcome, or the result may be fixed. The results are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">d12 score equal to/less than the number indicated: <strong>T (turned)</strong></span></li>\n<li>d12 score greater than the number indicated: <strong>NT (not turned)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Undead Turning Definitions:</strong><br>The following definitions apply to Table 13:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><strong>NT (not turned):</strong> the undead are beyond the cleric&rsquo;s power to affect.</span></li>\n<li><strong>T (turned):</strong> 2d6 undead are compelled to cower/flee for 1 turn unless attacked.</li>\n<li><strong>D (destroyed):</strong> 2d6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n<li><strong>UD (ultimate destruction):</strong> 1d6+6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>N.B.: Clerics of above-average charisma (15+) are more commanding; hence, their chance-in-twelve of success is improved by one (+1); e.g., a 4-in-12 chance becomes 5-in-12 (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>charisma</em>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Frequency of Undead Turning:</strong> This ability can be used a number of times per day equal to the character&rsquo;s TA; however, the cleric can make but one attempt per encounter unless a second wave of undead arrive.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 13: Turn Undead</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p. 33]</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>How to Turn Multiple Undead Types:</strong> If multiple kinds of undead are met in a single encounter, only one d12 roll is required. The same result is applied to each <em>Undead Type</em>. Those of the lowest <em>Undead Type</em> are affected first, unless the sorcerer specifically targets a single creature, in which case only that creature potentially is affected (e.g., if a <strong>vampire</strong> stands at the fore of a pack of <strong>zombies</strong>, the cleric might step forth, holy symbol raised, and speak a commandment of abolishment, pointing a holy symbol directly at the <strong>vampire</strong>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Evil Command of Undead:</strong> A cleric of Evil alignment may opt to exercise control over the undead on a successful <em>turn undead</em> check. Such undead remain under the sorcerer&rsquo;s sway unless <em>turned</em> or <em>commanded</em> by another sorcerer of equal or greater turning ability. Up to 2 HD of undead per TA level can be controlled. If a Neutral cleric attempts to <em>command undead</em>, then he or she will have turned to a darker path, submitting to Evil and no longer of Neutral alignment; consequences may ensue.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"cleric","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579090104,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"0lPqTsFlKtpS1lVq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Sorcery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Clerics memorize and cast spells, but they do not maintain spell books; rather, they might bear the scriptures of their faiths in prayer books, on sacred scrolls, or on graven tablets. The number and levels of spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 12</strong>, though clerics of high wisdom gain bonus spells cast per day (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>wisdom</em>). For example, a 4th-level cleric with 13 wisdom can cast three level 1 spells and two level 2 spells per day.</p>\n<p>Clerics begin their careers with knowledge of three level 1 spells, sacred mysteries revealed through initiation into a sect or cult devoted to an otherworldly power, deific being, or ethos. These spells are drawn from the <strong>Cleric Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 99</strong>). Clerics develop three new spells at each level gain, but they must be of castable levels (see <strong>Table 12</strong>). Typically, they are acquired via spiritual revelation, otherworldly favour, or the piecing together of abstract theologies. Such spells are learnt automatically, with no need of qualification rolls.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial no. of spells known: &times;3</li>\n<li>No. of spells gained per level: &times;3</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additional spells may be learnt outside of level training, but the process is more arduous (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>acquiring new spells</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"cleric","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579090104,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"2cvRspLTZFP8XsSO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke scrolls with spells from the <strong>Cleric Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 99</strong>), unless the scroll was created by a thaumaturgical sorcerer (one who casts magician or magician subclass spells).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"cleric","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PLRVII62fOX22khR"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579090103,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"HkmGJfxFS2ya7ywi","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Writing","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 32\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To scribe a known spell onto a scroll, creating a single-use magical device at a cost of 500 gp + 100 gp per spell level. Materials vary: Some clerics engrave thin tablets of stone, whereas others use vellum or parchment, a fine quill, and sorcerer&rsquo;s ink, such as sepia. This involved process requires one week per spell level and must be completed on consecrated ground, such as a shrine, fane, or temple.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"cleric","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5svHxLHi8sIn35Uj"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251303706,"modifiedTime":1681579090103,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"yI7R1SOSWXvksub9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
